{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885027306,"sessionID":"ses_28501d68affecc4q91rWzEACHL","part":{"id":"prt_d7aff0396001N6gnfjtxX1yMGT","messageID":"msg_d7afef73b0012scKWN3MDkvtIF","sessionID":"ses_28501d68affecc4q91rWzEACHL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0dc1765c6e474e9f90f775a667f93cf2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","limit":200,"offset":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n100: - **GIVEN** the CLI source code in cmd/cli/\n101: - **WHEN** running `make build-cli`\n102: - **THEN** CLI binary SHALL be compiled\n103: - **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/agentcube\n104: - **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n105: - **AND** the binary SHALL respond to --version flag\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Go build supports cross-platform compilation\n108: - **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n109: - **WHEN** setting GOOS and GOARCH environment variables\n110: - **THEN** the build SHALL compile for the target platform\n111: - **AND** the binary SHALL be placed in bin/<platform>/ subdirectory\n112: - **AND** supported platforms SHALL include: linux/amd64, linux/arm64, darwin/amd64, darwin/arm64\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Go build supports release mode\n115: - **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n116: - **WHEN** setting BUILD_MODE=release\n117: - **THEN** build flags SHALL include -ldflags=\"-s -w\" for stripping\n118: - **AND** debug information SHALL be removed\n119: - **AND** the binary size SHALL be minimized\n120: - **AND** the binary SHALL be production-ready\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Go build supports dev mode with race detection\n123: - **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n124: - **WHEN** setting BUILD_MODE=dev (default)\n125: - **THEN** build flags SHALL include -race for race detection\n126: - **AND** debug information SHALL be included\n127: - **AND** the binary SHALL be suitable for development\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Go build uses build cache efficiently\n130: - **GIVEN** a previous successful build\n131: - **WHEN** running `make build-go` again without source changes\n132: - **THEN** the build SHALL use cached artifacts\n133: - **AND** the build time SHALL be significantly faster\n134: - **AND** \"cache hit\" messages SHALL be displayed\n135: \n136: ### Requirement: Python build targets\n137: \n138: The system SHALL provide comprehensive build targets for Python packages in the AgentCube project.\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: build-python target builds Python package\n141: - **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project with Python source code\n142: - **WHEN** running `make build-python`\n143: - **THEN** the Python package SHALL be built as wheel\n144: - **AND** the wheel SHALL be placed in dist/ directory\n145: - **AND** the source distribution (sdist) SHALL also be built\n146: - **AND** build SHALL complete successfully\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: install-python target installs Python dependencies\n149: - **GIVEN** a Python environment with pip\n150: - **WHEN** running `make install-python`\n151: - **THEN** all production dependencies SHALL be installed\n152: - **AND** dependencies SHALL be read from requirements.txt or pyproject.toml\n153: - **AND** installation SHALL complete without errors\n154: - **AND** installed packages SHALL be listed\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: install-dev target installs development dependencies\n157: - **GIVEN** a Python environment with pip\n158: - **WHEN** running `make install-dev`\n159: - **THEN** all development dependencies SHALL be installed\n160: - **AND** dependencies SHALL include: pytest, ruff, mypy, black\n161: - **AND** installation SHALL complete without errors\n162: - **AND** development environment SHALL be ready\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Python build uses virtual environment\n165: - **GIVEN** the Python build targets\n166: - **WHEN** VIRTUAL_ENV environment variable is set\n167: - **THEN** the build SHALL use the virtual environment's Python\n168: - **AND** packages SHALL be installed in the virtual environment\n169: - **AND** the virtual environment SHALL not be affected by system Python\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Python build respects PYTHON_VERSION variable\n172: - **GIVEN** the Python build targets\n173: - **WHEN** setting PYTHON_VERSION to a specific version (e.g., 3.11)\n174: - **THEN** the build SHALL use the specified Python version\n175: - **AND** the version SHALL be validated\n176: - **AND** an error SHALL occur if the version is not available\n177: \n178: ### Requirement: Test targets\n179: \n180: The system SHALL provide comprehensive test targets for running Go and Python tests.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: test target runs all tests\n183: - **GIVEN** a built AgentCube project\n184: - **WHEN** running `make test`\n185: - **THEN** `make test-go` SHALL be invoked\n186: - **AND** `make test-python` SHALL be invoked\n187: - **AND** all tests SHALL pass\n188: - **AND** test summary SHALL be displayed with pass/fail counts\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: test-go target runs Go tests\n191: - **GIVEN** the Go source code with tests\n192: - **WHEN** running `make test-go`\n193: - **THEN** all Go tests SHALL be executed\n194: - **AND** tests SHALL run with verbose output (-v flag)\n195: - **AND** test coverage SHALL be collected\n196: - **AND** test results SHALL be summarized\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: test-python target runs Python tests\n199: - **GIVEN** the Python source code with tests\n200: - **WHEN** running `make test-python`\n201: - **THEN** all Python tests SHALL be executed using pytest\n202: - **AND** tests SHALL run with verbose output\n203: - **AND** test coverage SHALL be collected\n204: - **AND** test results SHALL be summarized\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: test-integration target runs integration tests\n207: - **GIVEN** the integration test suite\n208: - **WHEN** running `make test-integration`\n209: - **THEN** integration tests SHALL be executed\n210: - **AND** required services SHALL be started (if needed)\n211: - **AND** tests SHALL verify end-to-end functionality\n212: - **AND** test results SHALL be summarized\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: test-coverage target generates coverage reports\n215: - **GIVEN** the test suite with coverage enabled\n216: - **WHEN** running `make test-coverage`\n217: - **THEN** test coverage SHALL be collected for Go\n218: - **AND** test coverage SHALL be collected for Python\n219: - **AND** coverage reports SHALL be generated\n220: - **AND** coverage percentage SHALL be displayed\n221: - **AND** coverage SHALL meet the minimum threshold (e.g., 70%)\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: test-race target runs Go tests with race detection\n224: - **GIVEN** the Go source code with tests\n225: - **WHEN** running `make test-race`\n226: - **THEN** tests SHALL run with -race flag enabled\n227: - **AND** race conditions SHALL be detected if present\n228: - **AND** test execution SHALL complete (slower than normal tests)\n229: - **AND** no race conditions SHALL be reported in a healthy codebase\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: Tests can be run with specific package paths\n232: - **GIVEN** the test targets\n233: - **WHEN** specifying a package path (e.g., make test-go PKG=./pkg/router)\n234: - **THEN** only tests in the specified package SHALL run\n235: - **AND** the package path SHALL be validated\n236: - **AND** test results SHALL be displayed for the specified package\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Tests support parallel execution\n239: - **GIVEN** the test targets\n240: - **WHEN** running with -j flag (make -j test)\n241: - **THEN** Go and Python tests SHALL run in parallel\n242: - **AND** test execution SHALL complete faster\n243: - **AND** no test interference SHALL occur\n244: - **AND** test results SHALL be aggregated correctly\n245: \n246: ### Requirement: Code quality targets (lint, format)\n247: \n248: The system SHALL provide comprehensive code quality targets for linting and formatting code.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: lint target runs all lint checks\n251: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with source code\n252: - **WHEN** running `make lint`\n253: - **THEN** `make lint-go` SHALL be invoked\n254: - **AND** `make lint-python` SHALL be invoked\n255: - **AND** all lint checks SHALL pass\n256: - **AND** lint summary SHALL be displayed\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: lint-go target runs Go lint checks\n259: - **GIVEN** the Go source code\n260: - **WHEN** running `make lint-go`\n261: - **THEN** golangci-lint SHALL be executed\n262: - **AND** all Go files SHALL be checked\n263: - **AND** lint errors SHALL be reported with file and line numbers\n264: - **AND** exit code SHALL be non-zero if lint errors exist\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: lint-python target runs Python lint checks\n267: - **GIVEN** the Python source code\n268: - **WHEN** running `make lint-python`\n269: - **THEN** ruff SHALL be executed for linting\n270: - **AND** all Python files SHALL be checked\n271: - **AND** lint errors SHALL be reported with file and line numbers\n272: - **AND** exit code SHALL be non-zero if lint errors exist\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: format target formats all code\n275: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube project with source code\n276: - **WHEN** running `make format`\n277: - **THEN** `make format-go` SHALL be invoked\n278: - **AND** `make format-python` SHALL be invoked\n279: - **AND** all code SHALL be formatted according to standards\n280: - **AND** formatting summary SHALL be displayed\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: format-go target formats Go code\n283: - **GIVEN** the Go source code\n284: - **WHEN** running `make format-go`\n285: - **THEN** goimports SHALL be executed\n286: - **AND** imports SHALL be organized and sorted\n287: - **AND** code SHALL be formatted with gofmt standards\n288: - **AND** modified files SHALL be listed\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: format-python target formats Python code\n291: - **GIVEN** the Python source code\n292: - **WHEN** running `make format-python`\n293: - **THEN** black SHALL be executed\n294: - **AND** code SHALL be formatted according to PEP 8\n295: - **AND** modified files SHALL be listed\n296: - **AND** no formatting changes SHALL be made if code is already formatted\n297: \n298: #### Scenario: check target runs all quality checks\n299: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube project\n\n(Showing lines 100-299 of 959. Use offset=300 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- **GIVEN** the CLI source code in cmd/cli/\n- **WHEN** running `make build-cli`\n- **THEN** CLI binary SHALL be compiled\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/agentcube\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n- **AND** the binary SHALL respond to --version flag\n\n#### Scenario: Go build supports cross-platform compilation\n- **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n- **WHEN** setting GOOS and GOARCH environment variables\n- **THEN** the build SHALL compile for the target platform\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be placed in bin/<platform>/ subdirectory\n- **AND** supported platforms SHALL include: linux/amd64, linux/arm64, darwin/amd64, darwin/arm64\n\n#### Scenario: Go build supports release mode\n- **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n- **WHEN** setting BUILD_MODE=release\n- **THEN** build flags SHALL include -ldflags=\"-s -w\" for stripping\n- **AND** debug information SHALL be removed\n- **AND** the binary size SHALL be minimized","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775885027280,"end":1775885027304}}}}
